text: The Cadillac XT5 (short for Crossover Touring 5) is a compact luxury / D-segment crossover SUV. It has been made from 2016 to the present day by General Motors. The XT5 is made at GM's Spring Hill Manufacturing plant and the Chinese-market XT5 is made in Shanghai by SAIC-GM. The XT5 replaced the Cadillac SRX crossover. As of 2017, the XT5 was Cadillac's best selling model in the United States and globally. ==References== * ==Other websites== * XT5 Category:2010s automobiles Category:2020s automobiles
